                        <li><strong>Company Assets and Value</strong><br />Understanding the value of the business gives the stakeholders of the company to obtain information and knowledge about the company's assets and their actual weight.</li>
                        <li><strong>Bad Debt Accounting</strong><br />The unfortunate fact of having a bad debt in a business cannot be avoided. This kind of debt will likewise be reflected in the company’s financial statements. However, with the help of the business valuation, a company may get a better hold on bad debt.</li>
                        <li><strong>Company’s Cash Flow</strong><br />The company's cash flow can be determined and understood through a business valuation. In addition, it can lead the business owners to be informed on how to measure any discrepancy in the financial reporting.</li>
                        <li><strong>Resale Value</strong><br />Considering selling the company in the future, the business valuation is crucial since it will determine how much money you can get from selling it.</li>
                        <li><strong>Company Restructuring</strong><br />The business valuation determines the company's current worth, which in the long run will help in restructuring the company as and when required.</li>
                    </ol>
